<font color="#FF0000">WAR AND DNA</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jul 27  5:31:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
War is in the genes of man. Those who fight it, often chose to and feel obliged to. And I am grateful for those who are willing to fight for the good cause (whichever that may be). The fact that you keep on fighting in such a near ground manner (on the site), stems either from your experience as veterans or from the same genetical flaw that creates the love of war. <br><br>
Vietnam had a good reason to be fought. People who disagree should at least be able to understand why it was fought and why people believed it should be. Otherwise they close their eyes to history ('Peace in our time', Chamberlain, 1938).<br><br>

<p><code>-- eddo@eng.tau.ac.il  (Eddo) </code><p>


